cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new training paradigm for improving adversarial robustness in deep learning models. It may also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as adversarial robustness is a common concern in image classification tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. It may also be relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as adversarial attacks are a security concern in machine learning. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it proposes a new training method for neural networks.
